collation.p: The last leaf, without foliation, is folded around quires 19 and 20 and is visible as a stub onto which is added in quire 19. VisColl collation.

p.note: Note in Swedish regarding the acquisition of the book, in black ink by a ninetheenth-century-hand: Skänkt till Kongl. Bibliotheket af Ryttmästaren P. von Möller. 20 Oct. 1871. Har tillhört Lüdekes boksamling. är skrifvet i Sverige 1450-1500. National Library book label with the current signum in black ink.

history.provenance: Early provenance unknown. On account of the saints in the litany, a former librarian suggests that it was produced for use in Västerås diocese, but this seems uncertain since both St Botvid and St Katarina of Vadstena are listed in the litany, both of whom not in the Västerås calendar.

note.p: There may be parts missing from the beginning as the psalter only contains material for Sunday, Vespers for the weekdays and Compline.

p.note: A note in Swedish to the effect that the text marked by the black strokes here and on is identical to those in a book here referred to, Fernebo latinska bok, printed in 1525. In black ink by an eighteenth-century (?) hand: Från detta tvärstrek til nästa är det, hvad här emellan förekommer lika med art: Psalmi penitentianales i Fernebo latinska Bok Tryckt 1525.

A note in Swedish commenting on the fact that Katarina of Vadstena is present here but not (?) in the printed text, referred to in the previous addition. In black ink by an eighteenth-century hand: En Caterina de Wastenis är här mer än i den tryckta.

A note in Swedish on saints in the printed litany, not present here. In black ink by an eighteenth century hand: Uti den tryckta litanien äro införde: Erasm. Christoph.? Karlange? Brynolph och Praxedis hvilka här saknas, äfven Thomas.

A note in Swedish remarking on the textual similarity of the prayer here and in the printed volume referred to earlier. In black ink by an eighteenth-century hand: Denna Bön finnes och i den tryckta Boken med liten variation af ett och annat ord.

Information in Swedish to the effect that the texts on the preceding eight leaves are printed in a book with the title: Sequuntur nunc vigilie morturoum. In black ink by a modern hand: Alt hvad de föregående 8 Blad innehålla til slutet på denna sida, finnes med flere mellansatte sångstycken: antiph: Respons: och V. uti den Tryckta Boken under Tit: Sequuntur nunc vigilie mortuorum se Bl. Jvi Sid 2.

Information in Swedish about the existence of a printed version of the preceding prayer. In black ink by a modern hand: Föregående Bön, kallas i den tryckta anonyma Fernebo Boken Oratio de Domina och finnes där utförligare.
